<h2>Plugins</h2>
<p>
	Crux allows you to create plugins that can interupt certain parts of the normal flow to make your own changes to
	how the framework runs. For example, Crux comes with a built-in plugin for User-Agent string parsing which has to
	run everytime a request is made. Plugins can be created to perform an action as the framework initializes or as
	requests come in. To create a plugin, create a file in the <code>./plugins</code> directory. Then you can use the
	function <var>$.plugins.bind</var> to attach the plugin to the system.
</p>
<%- pre('code', [
	'$.plugins.bind("init", function() {',
	'',
	'    // do stuff after the core initializes',
	'',
	'});',
	'',
	'$.plugins.bind("request", function(handle) {',
	'',
	'    // do stuff everytime a request occurs',
	'',
	'});'
]) %>
<p>
	Once you have created your plugin, you can add the plugin to the <code>./config/plugins.json</code> config file.
</p>
<%- pre('code', [
	'// Plugin config file',
	'',
	'{',
	'    // Adds user-agent parsing the handle object',
	'    "useragent": true,',
	'',
	'    // Setting this to true enables the plugin; false disables it',
	'    "your-plugin": true',
	'}',
	'',
	'// End of file plugins.json',
	'// Location: ./config/plugins.json'
]) %>
